  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Permissions of type `endowment` currently do not support caveats at all; the `allowedCaveats` of their specification objects must be `null`. This is because we didn't need caveats for the first endowment permissions that we shipped. Recently, the Snaps team has started designing endowment permissions with rather lengthy \"arguments\" in their `snap.manifest.json`, for example the proposed `snap:keyring` permission: https://github.com/MetaMask/SIPs/blob/ba0540aed6e30ccb12c3743107d9280d2be78e7b/SIPS/sip-2.md#manifest\r\n\r\nThese \"arguments\" are essentially caveats, and they should be stored in the `PermissionController` state. Therefore, we to add support for caveats to endowment permissions.",
